tt0097441: Robert Gould Shaw leads the U.S. Civil War's first all-black volunteer company, fighting prejudices from both his own Union Army, and the Confederates.
tt0100519: Two minor characters from the play 'Hamlet' stumble around unaware of their scripted lives and unable to deviate from them.
tt0079522: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.
tt0100150: Tom Regan, an advisor to a Prohibition-era crime boss, tries to keep the peace between warring mobs but gets caught in divided loyalties.
tt0097165: English teacher John Keating inspires his students to look at poetry with a different perspective of authentic knowledge and feelings.
tt0061722: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.
tt0052311: A stark, perverse story of murder, kidnapping, and police corruption in a Mexican border town.
tt0100263: Convicted felon Nikita, instead of going to jail, is given a new identity and trained, stylishly, as a top secret spy/assassin.
tt0050212: After settling his differences with a Japanese PoW camp commander, a British colonel co-operates to oversee his men's construction of a railway bridge for their captors - while oblivious to a plan by the Allies to destroy it.
tt0056801: A harried movie director retreats into his memories and fantasies.
tt0071315: A private detective hired to expose an adulterer finds himself caught up in a web of deceit, corruption, and murder.
tt0043456: An alien lands and tells the people of Earth that they must live peacefully or be destroyed as a danger to other planets.
tt0040897: Fred Dobbs and Bob Curtin, two Americans searching for work in Mexico, convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.
tt0092610: The population of a small town disappears and is replaced by aliens that chase human flesh for their intergalactic fast-food chain.
tt0023969: Rufus T. Firefly is named president/dictator of bankrupt Freedonia and declares war on neighboring Sylvania over the love of wealthy Mrs. Teasdale.
tt0088794: A teenager has to deal with his girlfriend dumping him among family crises, homicidal paper boys, and a rival skier.
tt0081505: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter where an evil spiritual presence influences the father into violence, while his psychic son sees horrific forebodings from the past and of the future.
tt0092005: After the death of a friend, a writer recounts a boyhood journey to find the body of a missing boy.
tt0022100: When the police in a German city are unable to catch a child-murderer, other criminals join in the manhunt.
tt0092991: The lone survivor of an onslaught of flesh-possessing spirits holes up in a cabin with a group of strangers while the demons continue their attack.
tt0057115: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.
tt0077416: An in-depth examination of the ways in which the U.S. Vietnam War impacts and disrupts the lives of people in a small industrial town in Pennsylvania.
tt0082269: Two tapes, two Parisian mob killers, one corrupt policeman, an opera fan, a teenage thief, and the coolest philosopher ever filmed. All these characters twist their way through an intricate and stylish French language thriller.
tt0107048: A weatherman finds himself inexplicably living the same day over and over again.
tt0105695: Retired Old West gunslinger William Munny reluctantly takes on one last job, with the help of his old partner and a young man.
tt0056218: A former prisoner of war is brainwashed as an unwitting assassin for an international Communist conspiracy.
tt0100436: Mark runs a pirate radio station and causes an uproar when he speaks his mind and enthralls fellow teens.
tt0036613: A drama critic learns on his wedding day that his beloved maiden aunts are homicidal maniacs, and that insanity runs in his family.
tt0088763: Marty McFly, a 17-year-old high school student, is accidentally sent thirty years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend, the maverick scientist Doc Brown.
tt0101921: A housewife who is unhappy with her life befriends an old lady in a nursing home and is enthralled by the tales she tells of people she used to know.
tt0066206: The World War II phase of the career of the controversial American general, George S. Patton.
tt0090967: Two innocent people are arrested. An interesting third person, with broken English, joins them in their cell. On his idea, they decide to escape from the prison. Their journey is the rest of the movie.
tt0094625: A secret military project endangers Neo-Tokyo when it turns a biker gang member into a rampaging psychic psychopath that only two teenagers and a group of psychics can stop.
tt0091203: An immortal Scottish swordsman must confront the last of his immortal opponent, a murderously brutal barbarian who lusts for the fabled "Prize".
tt0061512: A laid back Southern man is sentenced to two years in a rural prison, but refuses to conform.
tt0099334: Embarrassed by his large nose, a romantic poet/soldier romances his cousin by proxy.
tt0072431: An American grandson of the infamous scientist, struggling to prove that his grandfather was not as insane as people believe, is invited to Transylvania, where he discovers the process that reanimates a dead body.
tt0102536: An anthology of 5 different cab drivers in 5 American and European cities and their remarkable fares on the same eventful night.
